---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const effectiveDate = "May 31, 2026";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Campus XI Privacy Policy covering sign-in, profile data, app activity, storage permission, and payments."
>
  <section class="hero-panel hero-panel--compact">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>
      <p class="hero-text">
        This explains what Campus XI collects, how it uses that information,
        and the choices available to users of the app.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell legal-shell">
    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Sign-In and Account Information</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Firebase Authentication account ID</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Display name or profile name shared by Google or Apple</li>
        <li>Profile photo URL, if shared by the sign-in provider</li>
        <li>Sign-in provider details, such as Google or Apple</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Campus XI uses Firebase Authentication with Google Sign-In and Apple
        Sign-In. We collect only the account information needed to create and
        manage the user account in the app.
      </p>
      <p class="notice">
        While Campus XI keeps personal data collection light, account details
        such as email address, profile name, and team name are still personal
        data.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Profile Data</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Team name chosen by the user</li>
        <li>Squad selections and fantasy team activity</li>
        <li>Points, rankings, and leaderboard position</li>
        <li>Event and tournament participation</li>
        <li>Premium pass status and related feature access</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information is used to operate the fantasy football experience,
        including scoring, team management, leaderboard display, and premium
        feature access.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Purchases, Passes, and Upgrades</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Pass tier information, such as Bronze, Silver, or Gold</li>
        <li>Purchase status and purchase verification result</li>
        <li>Transaction or payment reference information</li>
        <li>Upgrade history between pass tiers</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We use this information to activate premium access, process upgrades,
        investigate failed verifications, and respond to support questions.
      </p>
      <p class="notice">
        Campus XI does not store full payment card details. Payments are
        handled by third-party payment or platform providers.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Device Access and Saved Cards</h2>
      <p>
        Campus XI may ask for device permission when a user chooses to save a
        performance card or similar image to their gallery.
      </p>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>We allow user-requested saving to the device gallery.</li>
        <li>We do not browse or import photos from the user's gallery.</li>
        <li>We do not collect the user's gallery contents.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>To provide sign-in, account access, and core app features.</li>
        <li>To create and manage teams, points, and leaderboards.</li>
        <li>To activate passes and premium tools after successful purchase.</li>
        <li>To support pass upgrades.</li>
        <li>To respond to support emails, purchase issues, and bug reports.</li>
        <li>To protect the app against abuse, fraud, and misuse.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Sharing and Service Providers</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Authentication is provided through Firebase and sign-in providers.</li>
        <li>Payment processing is handled by third-party payment partners or platform stores.</li>
        <li>We may share limited data with service providers only as needed to run the app.</li>
        <li>We do not sell personal information.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Retention and User Requests</h2>
      <p>
        We keep account and purchase records for as long as needed
        to operate the app, maintain security, resolve disputes, and comply
        with legal or accounting obligations.
      </p>
      <p>
        Users who want help with access, correction, or deletion requests can
        contact support. Some records may need to be retained for security,
        fraud prevention, or legal reasons.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we may
        revise the effective date and post the updated version in the app or on
        this website.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, account requests, or data concerns, email
        <a href="mailto:support@campusxi.com">support@campusxi.com</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
